6, 2014","format":false,"excerpt":"Ibn Abbas reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, would wear a red-striped cloak on the day of Eid. Source: al-Mu\u2019jam al-Awsat\u0323 lil-T\u0323abara\u0304ni\u0304 7609 Grade: Jayyid (very good) according to Al-Albani Al-Nawawi said, \u201cThe scholars agreed with Al-Shafi\u2019i that it is recommended to wear the best\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/wisdom-al-hikmah\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":36093,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2021\/05\/11\/companions-taqabbal-allah\/","url_meta":{"origin":25003,"position":1},"title":"Sahaba on Eid: May Allah accept from us and you","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"May 11, 2021","format":false,"excerpt":"Jubayr ibn Nufayr reported: The Companions of the Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, when they met each other on the day of Eid, they would say to each other, \u201cMay Allah accept good deeds from us and from you.\u201d Source: S\u0323ala\u0304t al-'\u012adayn lil-Mah\u0323a\u0304mili\u0304 2\/218 Grade: Hasan\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Righteousness \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Righteousness \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/righteousness-al-birr\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":19589,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2014\/07\/26\/seven-five-takbir-salat-eid\/","url_meta":{"origin":25003,"position":2},"title":"Hadith on Eid: Seven and five Takbir in Eid prayer","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"July 26, 2014","format":false,"excerpt":"'Amr ibn 'Awf reported: The Prophet, peace and blessings be upon him, would pronounce takbir during the Eid prayer seven times before the recitation in the first cycle, and five times before the recitation in the second cycle. Al-Tirmidhi said, \u201cThis tradition is acted upon by some of the people\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/wisdom-al-hikmah\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":19587,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2014\/07\/26\/ghusl-before-eid-prayer\/","url_meta":{"origin":25003,"position":3},"title":"Hadith on Eid: Perform Ghusl before attending Eid prayer","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"July 26, 2014","format":false,"excerpt":"Nafi\u2019 reported: Abdullah ibn Umar, may Allah be pleased with him, used to perform a ritual bath\u00a0on the day of Eid\u00a0before he would depart\u00a0for prayer. Source: al-Muwat\u0323t\u0323a' 609 Grade: Sahih (authentic) according to Al-Nawawi Imam al-Nawawi commented, \"The narrations of Al-Shafi'i and his companions agree upon the recommendation to perform\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/wisdom-al-hikmah\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":5394,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2012\/08\/19\/dua-for-eid\/","url_meta":{"origin":25003,"position":4},"title":"Abu Umamah on Eid: Companions ask Allah to accept good deeds","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"August 19, 2012","format":false,"excerpt":"Muhammad ibn Ziyad reported: I was with Abu Umamah al-Bahili and others among the Companions of the Prophet, peace and blessings be upon him. When they would return from Eid prayer, they would say to each other, \u201cMay Allah accept good deeds from us and from you.\u201d Imam Ahmad said,\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Scholars \u0627\u0644\u0639\u0644\u0645\u0627\u0621&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Scholars \u0627\u0644\u0639\u0644\u0645\u0627\u0621","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/scholars-ulema\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":19598,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2014\/07\/26\/eid-takbir-imam-arrives\/","url_meta":{"origin":25003,"position":5},"title":"Hadith on Eid: Pronouncing Takbir until the Imam arrives","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"July 26, 2014","format":false,"excerpt":"Nafi\u2019 reported: Abdullah ibn Umar, may Allah be pleased with him, would depart to the Eid prayer from the mosque and he would raise his voice, declaring the greatness of Allah until he arrived at the place of prayer. He would continue to exalt Allah until the Imam arrived. Source:\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Righteousness \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Righteousness \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/righteousness-al-birr\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]}],"_links":{"self":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/25003","targetHints":{"allow":["GET"]}}],"collection":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts"}],"about":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/types\/post"}],"author":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/users\/3712"}],"replies":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/comments?post=25003"}],"version-history":[{"count":0,"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadit